        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued May 8 at 6:00PM EDT by NWS Greenville-Spartanburg SC</headline>
        <description>At 600 PM EDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm 8
miles west of Hendersonville, or near Etowah, moving east at 15 mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 40 mph and penny size hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor hail damage to outdoor objects is
possible.

Locations impacted include...
Mills River, Flat Rock, Horse Shoe, Penrose, Etowah, Hendersonville,
Mountain Home, Forge Mountain, Valley Hill, and Fletcher.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.

A Severe Thunderstorm Watch remains in effect until midnight EDT for
western North Carolina.</instruction>
